## рџЊђ INTERNATIONALISATION (i18n) вЂ” MANDATORY RULES

**The site runs in three languages: Polish (primary), English, Ukrainian.**

### Library
- Use `i18next` + `react-i18next` + `i18next-browser-languagedetector`
- Configuration in `src/lib/i18n.ts`
- Default and fallback language: `pl`

### Translation structure
```
src/
в””в”Ђв”Ђ locales/
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ pl/
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ translation.json   # Polish (primary)
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ en/
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ translation.json   # English
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ uk/
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ translation.json   # Ukrainian
```

### Translation rules
- All user-visible strings MUST go through `t('key')` вЂ” no hardcoded text in components
- Keys in format `namespace.section.element`: `hero.title`, `pricing.standard.description`, `form.submit`
- Polish file is the source of truth: write Polish first, then translate to the others
- Never use `any` for translation types вЂ” generate types from the Polish file (e.g. `i18next-typescript`)

### Language switcher
- Component: `src/app/components/ui/LanguageSwitcher.tsx`
- Displays flags or codes: `PL | EN | UK`
- Placed in `<Navigation>` вЂ” visible on all pages
- Current language visually highlighted (active state)
- Touch target at least 44Г—44px
- On language change вЂ” page does NOT reload (SPA switch)

### URL strategy
- Language is stored in `localStorage` via `i18next-browser-languagedetector`
- URL stays without language prefix (`/pakiet-standard`, not `/pl/pakiet-standard`)
- Reason: static hosting, simple config; SEO handled via `hreflang`

### SEO + hreflang
- On every page, add `hreflang` tags in `<PageMeta>` for all three languages:
  - `<link rel="alternate" hreflang="pl" href="..." />`
  - `<link rel="alternate" hreflang="en" href="..." />`
  - `<link rel="alternate" hreflang="uk" href="..." />`
  - `<link rel="alternate" hreflang="x-default" href="..." />` (points to Polish)
- `<title>` and `<meta name="description">` are always in the active language

### Component rules
- Never write text directly in JSX вЂ” only via `useTranslation()`
- Image `alt` text also via `t()`
- Dates, numbers, currencies вЂ” format with `Intl` using locale (`pl-PL`, `en-GB`, `uk-UA`)
- Text direction: all three languages are LTR вЂ” no extra logic needed

### Example
```tsx
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';

export const HeroSection = () => {
  const { t } = useTranslation();

  return (
    <section aria-label={t('hero.ariaLabel')}>
      <h1>{t('hero.title')}</h1>
      <p>{t('hero.subtitle')}</p>
    </section>
  );
};
```

