## рџ—„пёЏ POCKETBASE INTEGRATION вЂ” RULES

### Purpose
PocketBase is used as a lightweight backend-as-a-service for:
- Storing all form submissions (leads) for admin review
- Enabling admins to update lead status (new в†’ contacted в†’ closed)
- Future-proofing: content edits (packages, pricing) without code changes

### Architecture
- PocketBase SDK lives in `src/lib/pocketbase.ts` вЂ” singleton instance
- All PocketBase calls go through `src/services/leads.ts`
- Never call PocketBase directly from components вЂ” always through the service layer

### Setup (`src/lib/pocketbase.ts`)

```ts
import PocketBase from 'pocketbase';

// Singleton вЂ” one instance for the whole app
export const pb = new PocketBase(import.meta.env.VITE_POCKETBASE_URL);

// Auto-refresh token if using admin auth
pb.autoCancellation(false);
```

### Environment Variables

```env
VITE_POCKETBASE_URL=https://your-pocketbase-instance.com
```

### Collection Structure

**Collection: `leads`**

| Field         | Type     | Required | Notes                              |
|--------------|----------|----------|------------------------------------|
| `name`        | Text     | вњ…       | Applicant name                     |
| `phone`       | Text     | вњ…       | Phone number                       |
| `package_type`| Select   | вќЊ       | `standard` / `premium`             |
| `message`     | Text     | вќЊ       | Optional message                   |
| `status`      | Select   | вњ…       | `new` / `contacted` / `closed`     |
| `source`      | Text     | вќЊ       | UTM or page slug                   |
| `created`     | DateTime | auto     | Auto-set by PocketBase             |

### Service Layer (`src/services/leads.ts`)

```ts
import { pb } from '@/lib/pocketbase';
import type { LeadPayload } from './telegram';

export interface Lead extends LeadPayload {
  id: string;
  status: 'new' | 'contacted' | 'closed';
  created: string;
}

export async function saveLeadToPocketBase(payload: LeadPayload): Promise<Lead> {
  return pb.collection('leads').create<Lead>({
    ...payload,
    status: 'new',
  });
}

export async function updateLeadStatus(id: string, status: Lead['status']): Promise<Lead> {
  return pb.collection('leads').update<Lead>(id, { status });
}
```

### Data Flow: Form Submission

```
User fills form
  в†’ useContactForm.submit(payload)
    в†’ sendLeadToTelegram(payload)   [notify admin immediately]
    в†’ saveLeadToPocketBase(payload) [persist for future reference]
    в†’ setState('success')
```

Both operations run in sequence. If Telegram fails вЂ” the lead is still saved to PocketBase. If PocketBase fails вЂ” the admin was still notified via Telegram. Handle partial failures gracefully.

### Error Strategy
- Log both failures separately with context
- Show the user a generic error message вЂ” never expose API errors
- Consider wrapping both in `Promise.allSettled` if you want parallel execution:

```ts
const [telegramResult, pbResult] = await Promise.allSettled([
  sendLeadToTelegram(payload),
  saveLeadToPocketBase(payload),
]);

if (telegramResult.status === 'rejected') {
  console.error('[form] Telegram failed:', telegramResult.reason);
}
if (pbResult.status === 'rejected') {
  console.error('[form] PocketBase failed:', pbResult.reason);
}

// Only show error to user if BOTH failed
if (telegramResult.status === 'rejected' && pbResult.status === 'rejected') {
  throw new Error('Both integrations failed');
}
```

