## рџ’» CODING STANDARDS

### General
- Write self-documenting code вЂ” names should explain intent
- Functions do ONE thing and do it well (SRP)
- Max function length: ~40 lines. If longer вЂ” refactor
- Max file length: ~300 lines. If longer вЂ” split into modules
- No magic numbers вЂ” use named constants
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Fail fast вЂ” validate inputs early and loudly
- **All code and documentation comments must be in English** (including HTML comments and JSDoc/TSDoc).

### Naming Conventions
- Components: `PascalCase` в†’ `UserProfileCard.tsx`
- Hooks: `camelCase` with `use` prefix в†’ `useContactForm.ts`
- Services: `camelCase` в†’ `telegram.ts`, `leads.ts`
- Utilities: `camelCase` в†’ `formatCurrency.ts`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` в†’ `MAX_RETRY_COUNT`
- Types/Interfaces: `PascalCase` в†’ `LeadPayload`, `ApiResponse<T>`
- CSS classes: `kebab-case` or BEM в†’ `user-card__avatar--active`
- Routes: `kebab-case` в†’ `/pakiet-standard`
- Files: match the main export name

### TypeScript
- Strict mode always enabled
- No `any` вЂ” use `unknown` and narrow types properly
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections
- Generic types where reusability makes sense
- Enums for finite sets of values
- Zod for runtime validation at form submission boundaries

### Error Handling
- Never swallow errors silently
- Always log errors with context (module, function, input shape)
- Use custom error classes for domain errors when appropriate
- Return `Result<T, E>` pattern for expected failures where it fits
- Unexpected errors bubble up to global error boundary

### Async
- Prefer `async/await` over `.then()` chains
- Always handle promise rejections
- Use `Promise.allSettled` for parallel independent async operations where partial failure is acceptable
- Add timeouts for all external calls (Telegram API, PocketBase)

---

## рџ“± MOBILE-FIRST & RESPONSIVE

### Core principle: Mobile is default. Desktop is an enhancement.

### CSS approach:
- Always start styles for mobile (min-width: 0)
- Scale up with breakpoints: `sm (640px)`, `md (768px)`, `lg (1024px)`, `xl (1280px)`, `2xl (1536px)`
- Use relative units: `rem`, `em`, `%`, `vw/vh`, `clamp()`
- Avoid fixed pixel widths on containers

### Layout rules:
- Use CSS Grid for page layouts, Flexbox for component-level alignment
- Every block/component must be tested at: 320px, 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px
- Touch targets minimum 44Г—44px
- No horizontal scroll on mobile (`overflow-x: hidden` on root)
- Images: always responsive with `max-width: 100%`; use `srcSet` where needed
- Typography: fluid with `clamp()` вЂ” `font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem)`

### Component checklist:
- [ ] Works on 320px screen
- [ ] Touch-friendly (no hover-only interactions)
- [ ] No layout break between breakpoints
- [ ] Readable font sizes on all screens
- [ ] Images do not overflow

